.TH BTRFS-RECOVERY-TOOL 8 "June 2026" "v1.0.0" "Btrfs Recovery Cleaner & Merger"
.SH NAME
btrfs-recovery-tool \- Btrfs filesystem recovery, verification, deduplication and merging toolset
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B scan_subvols.py
[\-\-device DEVICE] [\-\-uuid UUID] [\-\-chunks CHUNKS]
.br
.B clean_recovery.py
[\-\-active-root PATH] [\-\-recovery-dir PATH] [\-\-recreated-dir-name NAME] [\-\-duplicates-dir-name NAME] [\-\-unmatched-dir-name NAME] [\-\-resume CHOICE] [\-\-archive CHOICE] [\-\-wipe CHOICE] [\-\-recheck-unmatched] [\-\-recheck-duplicates] [\-\-merge CHOICE]
.br
.B recovery_merge.py
[\-\-src PATH] [\-\-dst PATH] [\-\-log PATH]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B btrfs-recovery-tool
is a suite of Python scripts designed to assist in recovering, cleaning up, and merging data from corrupted Btrfs filesystems. It works in three distinct stages: scanning raw blocks for metadata trees, validating/deduplicating restored data against the active system, and safely merging the clean recovered files back into the active home directory without overwrites.
.SH STAGES
.TP
.B Stage 1: scan_subvols.py
Directly reads the raw block device (e.g., \fI/dev/sdX1\fR) and scans candidate Btrfs chunk offset ranges for metadata trees containing \fBROOT_ITEM\fR structures matching the specified filesystem UUID. It lists subvolumes, generations, and root tree blocks, which are suitable inputs to feed into the \fBbtrfs restore -t <block>\fR command.
.TP
.B Stage 2: clean_recovery.py
Verifies restored files against the active filesystem. It automatically restores wrongly recovered text-file symlinks, squashes matching directory symlinks (converting them to real directories to prevent circular loops), deduplicates identical files against the active disk, resolves unmatched folder paths from \fBlost+found\fR using file hierarchy matching, and separates remaining unmatched files.
.TP
.B Stage 3: recovery_merge.py
Recursively merges the cleaned recovery directory back into the active main filesystem. It moves recovered files atomically and never overwrites existing target files (collisions are skipped and logged). Broken target symlinks at the destination are safely replaced with recovered directories or files.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS scan_subvols.py Options
.TP
.BI \-\-device " DEVICE"
Specify the block device partition to scan (default: /dev/sdX1).
.TP
.BI \-\-uuid " UUID"
Specify the filesystem UUID to match (Required, e.g. 12345678-abcd-1234-abcd-1234567890ab).
.TP
.BI \-\-chunks " CHUNKS"
Comma-separated list of offset:length chunks to scan.
.SS clean_recovery.py Options
.TP
.BI \-\-active-root " PATH"
Path to the active filesystem directory to scan/dedup against (default: ~/).
.TP
.BI \-\-recovery-dir " PATH"
Path to the base recovery directory (default: ~/recovery).
.TP
.BI \-\-recreated-dir-name " NAME"
Subfolder name containing the recovered files (default: recreated_dir_tree).
.TP
.BI \-\-duplicates-dir-name " NAME"
Subfolder name to store duplicate files (default: duplicates).
.TP
.BI \-\-unmatched-dir-name " NAME"
Subfolder name to store unmatched lost+found folders (default: unmatched).
.TP
.BI \-\-resume " {y,n,a}"
Pre-specify the response to the unfinished run resume prompt (y: yes, n: no/delete, a: archive).
.TP
.BI \-\-archive " {y,n}"
Pre-specify the response to the archiving prompt (y: yes, n: no).
.TP
.BI \-\-wipe " {y,n}"
Pre-specify the response to the wipe leftovers prompt (y: yes, n: no).
.TP
.B \-\-recheck-unmatched
Skip standard verification and only recheck files inside the unmatched directory.
.TP
.B \-\-recheck-duplicates
Skip standard verification and scan the recovery tree for remaining duplicate files.
.TP
.BI \-\-merge " {y,n}"
Pre-specify the response to the automatic recovery merge prompt (y: yes, n: no).
.SS recovery_merge.py Options
.TP
.BI \-\-src " PATH"
Source recovery tree directory to merge from (default: ~/recovery/recreated_dir_tree).
.TP
.BI \-\-dst " PATH"
Destination main filesystem directory to merge into (default: ~/).
.TP
.BI \-\-log " PATH"
Log file path (default: ~/recovery/recovery_merge.log).
.SH FILES
.I ~/recovery/clean_recovery.log
.RS
Continuous per-run log file for the cleanup process.
.RE
.I ~/recovery/run_stats.json
.RS
JSON file storing cumulative statistics across cleanup runs.
